You can use this property to add additional fields to an API request that are not explicitly defined by the objects interface. This can be useful when using beta features that havent been added to the Stripe SDK yet. For example, if the /v1/tokens API began to accept a beta field called test_field, you might do the following:
var cardParams = STPCardParams()
// add card values
cardParams.additionalAPIParameters = [test_field: example_value]
STPAPIClient.shared.createToken(withParameters: cardParams completion:);
